rename.to: TFlite model crashes in ONNX runtime

body: The problem with the model is it is missing shape info for the graph inputs of a loop subgraph.  I'll fix it in the converter, but ORT should be updated to not crash in this case.

issue.title: Add check that Loop subgraph iter_num and cond inputs have a shape

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
Add check that the first 2 Loop subgraph inputs have an shape (could be explicit or inferred) as we need to know the rank the subgraph expects. Other inputs to the subgraph are more opaque so we can just pass them through.

We can't do the check earlier as the Loop inferencing doesn't see the subgraph, so can't check if the subgraph has an explicit shape. We can't add a check in the generic Graph::InferAndVerifySubgraphTypes as there are other scenarios where it's fine for there to be no shape (e.g. outer scope variable being used in a subgraph two levels down), and we don't want to be adding operator specific logic at that level.

Manually tested with model from #6874. 

**Motivation and Context**
Provides error message for #6874

body:
@skottmckay does your commit fix the issue? 
How can I test it using the python package?

No - my change will give an error message instead of crashing silently. 

You need an updated version of the tf2onnx converter to generate a correct model, at which point the model should work with the existing ORT python package.

Incidentally should the model start with a Reshape node or a Transpose? Looks like it's attempting to convert between NCHW and NHWC, but a Reshape won't do that (it just changes the shape not the data).
